cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as named entity recognition. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a multi-task learning approach and a mixture of entity experts framework. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing a model for a specific task. It may also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses neural networks for the proposed model. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as named entity recognition is a crucial task in information retrieval.
